The segmentation based on application further highlights the versatility of hemp seeds across various industries. In the food and beverages segment, hemp seeds are utilized in a wide range of products including salads, smoothies, protein bars, and dairy alternatives, catering to the growing demand for healthy and natural ingredients. The pharmaceutical sector is also incorporating hemp seeds for their potential health benefits, further expanding the market reach of hemp-based products. Additionally, hemp seeds are finding applications in personal care products such as lotions and shampoos due to their moisturizing properties, tapping into the trend of natural and sustainable beauty products.

Geographically, North America leads the global hemp seed market, driven by the increasing legalization of hemp cultivation and the growing consumer awareness of hemp-based products in the region. Europe also holds a significant market share, fueled by the rising demand for hemp products and the presence of key market players in the region. The Asia-Pacific region is witnessing rapid growth in the hemp seed market, driven by the increasing awareness of the health benefits of hemp seeds and the evolving dietary preferences of consumers in the region.

